23: +  Demo file format: demo is a text file with one record per line. If line
24: +  starts with '#', it is ignored. First line of a demo should be a comment
25: +  holding the FPS, resolution (due to mouse offsets) and version of the game
26: +  used to record the demo. If a line starts with '*', it will be rewinded
27: +  to this position when played back. Otherwise the line is of format:
28: +
29: +  F Z X Y
30: +  
31: +  where F is a non-negative frame number, X and Y are horizontal and vertical
32: +  mouse offsets (with possible sign), all in decimal, and Z is the button state
33: +  in format
34: +
35: +  PONMLKJIHGFEDCBA
36: +
37: +  where each letter is either 0 (not pressed) or 1 (pressed), A means key
